  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6593 sitting right between max negative gamma at 6590 (-25.9B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+20.3B), dealers are in a critical zone where they're likely buying the current level aggressively as short gamma forces them to chase momentum. The massive -68.6B total GEX in BREAKOUT regime means any move will be amplified by dealer hedging flows, with the 6590-6605 corridor acting as the fulcrum between accelerating selling pressure below and stabilizing forces above. Watch for explosive moves if we break cleanly through either 6590 (dealers accelerate buying into weakness) or 6605 (dealers flip to selling strength), with the gex_surge event suggesting we're at an inflection point.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile whipsaws between 6590-6605 until one side breaks decisively.",
